This paper deals with ranking algorithms and sample complexity analysis, which are common topics in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The use of pairwise and listwise queries also suggests a focus on learning to rank, which is a subfield of machine learning. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are the most likely sub-categories. The use of lower bounds and upper bounds also suggests a theoretical focus, which could fall under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.CC (Computational Complexity). Finally, the use of the multinomial logit model suggests a potential connection to information theory, which could fall under cs.IT (Information Theory).
